last_episode_to_air.overview: Unseen footage from season 7, with guests including Rachel Parris, Jason Byrne, London Hughes, Seann Walsh, Jessica Hynes, Ola Labib and Russell Kane.

name: Alan Davies: As Yet Untitled
overview: One of Britain’s favourite comedians doing what he does best – being funny. But Alan Davies isn’t on a stage, or behind his QI desk sparring with Stephen Fry, or even wearing his Jonathan Creek duffle coat… instead, Alan is at his most relaxed and most natural – sitting around chatting with some of his best comedian friends.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: A seventh series was recorded at the Battersea Arts Centre. It was broadcast starting in March 2023.

episodes.name: Cupped By A Shammy Hand
episodes.overview: No agenda or script, just rib-tickling improvised chat and amusing anecdotes with Alan Davies and his comic chums Noel Fielding, Jon Ronson, Andrew Maxwell and Kerry Godliman.

episodes.name: Sex is Fun
episodes.overview: No agenda or script, just rib-tickling improvised chat and amusing anecdotes with Alan Davies and his comic chums Jason Byrne, Richard Herring, Phill Jupitus, and Jessica Hynes.

episodes.name: The Bringer Of Spiders
episodes.overview: No agenda or script, just rib-tickling improvised chat and amusing anecdotes with Alan Davies and his comic chums Bob Mortimer, Marcus Brigstocke, Katherine Ryan, and Jon Robins.

episodes.name: Until I'm Married Or You're Dead
episodes.overview: No agenda or script, just rib-tickling improvised chat and amusing anecdotes with Alan Davies and his comic chums Bill Bailey, Kevin Eldon, Isy Suttie, and Craig Campbell.

episodes.name: Jarvis Cocker's Britpop Herd
episodes.overview: No agenda or script, just rib-tickling improvised chat and amusing anecdotes with Alan Davies and his comic chums Ross Noble, Liza Tarbuck, Colin Lane, and Josie Long.

episodes.name: Were you on the South Bank show last night?
episodes.overview: Compilation episode – "The Unseen Bits of Series 1"

episodes.name: Simple People Eating Complex Carbohydrates
episodes.overview: No agenda or script, just side-splitting improvised chat and amusing anecdotes with Alan Davies and his comedic chums Tommy Tiernan, Jimmy Carr, Seann Walsh and Holly Walsh.

episodes.name: The Pig Knows You're Frightened
episodes.overview: The curly-haired QI favourite hosts a hilarious free-form chat show, where the conversation can go anywhere! With Ben Miller, Lizzie Roper, Felicity Ward and Patrick Kielty.

episodes.name: Two Lesbians Pissed On By Bats
episodes.overview: Dave's exclusive chat show! Host Alan Davies is joined by gag-loving guests Sarah Millican, Stephen Mangan, Hal Cruttenden and Zoe Lyons for some quality unrehearsed banter.

episodes.name: A British Asian Comedian Can No Longer Afford To Buy A House Because of James Brown
episodes.overview: The acid test for all comedians - no scripts, no rehearsals and no agenda! David Baddiel, Sharon Horgan, James Brown and Nish Kumar join our Alan for some ad-libbed absurdity.

episodes.name: Thwarted Sex Pests
episodes.overview: Giggles guaranteed as QI's klaxon king invites guests Jo Brand, James Acaster, Ricky Tomlinson and Sara Pascoe to crowd round his table for a completely off-the-cuff chat.

episodes.name: Countryfile
episodes.overview: Anything goes as Alan Davies and guests Ross Noble, Janet Street-Porter, Angela Barnes and Michael Ball are given free reign to chinwag about Cher, crossbows and The Archers!

episodes.name: You Can Face Time Or You Can Face This
episodes.overview: Off the leash and unimpeded by Stephen Fry's points deductions, our Alan muses on Vegas marriages and hit singles with Johnny Vegas, David O'Doherty, Grace Dent and Sean Kelly.

episodes.name: My Father's Would Be Assassins
episodes.overview: 'Trending' tonight on Alan's own impromptu chat show: kitesurfing, car bombs and Sir Cliff! Jack Dee, Matthew Crosby, Shappi Khorsandi and Julian Clary join him for a natter.

episodes.name: Hello, Can I Have A Bath?
episodes.overview: Ardal O'Hanlon, Roisin Conaty, Rob Delaney and Elis James join Alan to chat about all the hot topics - like being heckled by Grandmaster Flash and serenaded by Lionel Richie!

episodes.name: The Land Of Happy Donkeys
episodes.overview: Marvellously meandering chat with Alan Davies and guests Jonathan Ross, Germaine Greer, Tom Wrigglesworth and Lucy Beaumont. 'Goat punching' is just one of their mad subjects!

episodes.name: Unseen: The Lips And Arseholes Of Alan Davies
episodes.overview: Previously unseen footage from the second series of the chat show, with highlights including Julian Clary explaining why he avoids readers of a certain magazine, and Johnny Vegas revealing his favourite comedian who never made it in showbusiness. Plus, Jack Dee tells the story of how he lost his car at a service station.

episodes.name: I've Been Fingered By Captain Kirk
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Katherine Jakeways, Lee Mack, Nick Helm and Olivia Lee to discuss such varied subjects as an incident involving the horse Red Rum and a car window, Olivia Lee's grandmother's love advice, an embarrassing meeting for Katherine Jakeways and getting fingered by Captain Kirk.

episodes.name: Thirty Five Quid For This...
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Matt Lucas, John Thomson, Sarah Kendall and Stuart Goldsmith to discuss such varied subjects as upsetting rock legends, impressions, an exploding spider's nest and why comedy and music don't go together.

episodes.name: I'm Locked In With A Ham And I'm Not Coming Out
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Aisling Bea, Justin Moorhouse, Jo Enright and Jim Moir (Vic Reeves) to discuss such varied subjects as living without central heating, performing stand up at weddings and mansions, stories of stealing, befriending old men, Jim's working with pigs experiences and being star-struck.

episodes.name: It Must Have Been Big To Serve A Lot Of People
episodes.overview: Alan and his guests Jon Robins, Russell Howard, Reece Shearsmith and Tiffany Stevenson discuss Freddie Mercury's penis-shaped birthday cake, cruel animal mishaps, John Robins' nudist beach experience, recovering after general anaesthetic and being caught out by technology.

episodes.name: That Is A Lie
episodes.overview: Alan and his guests Bill Bailey, Diane Morgan, Steve Pemberton and Romesh Ranganathan discuss such varied subjects as latex disasters, dental wonders, how rap and Indian food are not the greatest combination and how unashamed a certain celebrity is when going to the loo.

episodes.name: Watch Out, Wanky Bill's About
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Bob Mortimer, Russell Kane, Lucy Montgomery and Miles Jupp to discuss such varied subjects as sneaky cockroaches, Iranian fruit, how one can 'show off' in the gym a little too much, and potentially why milk at schools often tastes unusual.

episodes.name: Loose Men With Chris Martin
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Jo Brand, Chris Martin, Tommy Tiernan and Alun Cochrane to discuss such varied subjects as modern male grooming habits, dating unsuitable men, communicating with the 'other side' and using elongated periods of comedic wonderment to deal with anger management issues.

episodes.name: No Smiling, No Laughing
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Phill Jupitus, Stuart Maconie, Pippa Evans and Carl Donnelly to discuss such varied subjects as gleeking, bizarre urban myths within music, 'faking it, till you're making it' and being trapped in a lift with Nelly Furtado.

episodes.name: And Then He Deftly Grabbed My Cervix
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Jason Byrne, Denise Van Outen, Josh Widdicombe and Alice Levine to discuss such varied subjects as acts of charity (with a twist!), stealing from the Royal Family, tough crowds and how sitting down in the shower can lead to some serious consequences.

episodes.name: Jokes About James Joyce And Ballet
episodes.overview: Alan is joined by Charlie Higson, Sally Phillips, Johnny Vaughan and Ellie Taylor to discuss such varied subjects as Josh Hartnett, emergency escapes from oil rigs, acts of charity and the potential use of men's Spanx.

episodes.name: Out-takes: Nigel Farage
episodes.overview: Join Alan and all his guests from the series as we look at some of the great stories that didn't quite make it to the show. Among those we find out how Matt Lucas single-handedly destroyed a clothing brand in the UK, what happens when Russell Kane eats too much Tikka Masala and why Josh Widdicombe has a tattoo of the name 'Greg' on his foot.

episodes.name: Don't Know If It Was The Embarrassment Or The Narcotics But I Have a Nose Bleed
episodes.overview: Stephen Fry, Sandi Toksvig, Sara Pascoe and Alex Edelman take their seats at the table revealing a range of personal stories including how to handle annoying neighbours, how to 'come out' and why the drugs definitely don't work.

episodes.name: A Clacker Free Zone
episodes.overview: Catherine Tate discusses her failings in the office and her fiery temper; Milton Jones reveals how he once caused a bloodbath, while performance artist Bryony Kimmings shares her thoughts on the nation's pubic hair. Ainsley Harriott, who definitely isn't Lenny Henry, completes the guest line up.

episodes.name: A Penis Poking Through The Window
episodes.overview: Alan Davies is joined by Lou Sanders; the stars of The IT Crowd, Richard Ayoade and Katherine Parkinson; plus star voice of The Simpsons, Harry Shearer. They discuss dying from embarrassment, strip clubs and the worst places to live.

episodes.name: Hitler & Jingle
episodes.overview: David Mitchell, Liza Tarbuck, Dane Baptiste and Lolly Adefope sit down with Alan for more directionless chitchat. While Dane and Lolly swap recipes, David opens up about his fear of crustaceans and Liza reveals the grizzly details surrounding Basil's death.

episodes.name: Just Pop a Knife Near Your Penis
episodes.overview: Jon Richardson, Mark Olver, Jenny Eclair and Alexei Sayle's conversation veers from female pattern baldness to Marxism, punk poetry and health & safety advice.

episodes.name: Jaffa Cake Nipples
episodes.overview: Alan invites Al Murray, Victoria Coren Mitchell, Luisa Omielan and Rob Beckett to join him for a feast of funny stories. The group discuss weird crushes, wacky weddings, anger management and abnormal nipples.

episodes.name: Just The Moon and My Mum's Tits
episodes.overview: Stephen K. Amos, Josh Howie, Bridget Christie and multi-marathon runner, Eddie Izzard, take their seats at the table with Alan for a chat involving tales concerning showbiz connections, bizarre gift ideas and erectile discomfort.

episodes.name: Carnal Happy Fun Times
episodes.overview: Jessica Hynes, Wes Borg, Deirdre O'Kane and Chris Addison take their seats at the table with Alan to discuss a diverse range of topics including operatic aspirations, broken appendages, and top tips on how to deal with brash Americans.

episodes.name: Do I Know Him? I Shagged Him!
episodes.overview: Mark Watson, Katy Wix, Karen Taylor and Jim Moir (aka Vic Reeves) join Alan Davies for another evening of impromptu chat. The conversation veers from crap competition wins and hideous surprises to faking it and freakish phobias.

episodes.name: Cream Cakes And Pernod
episodes.overview: Alan Davies invites Omid Djalili, Alex Horne, Shaun Ryder and Kathy Burke to join him for a feast of funny stories. From blisteringly honest tales of sex to drugs and fame no topic is off limits. Kathy and Alan open up about losing a parent and Omid reveals how fulfilling a dying wish went disastrously wrong.

episodes.name: Captain Kirk & William Shatner are Two Different People
They Burnt My Arse With a Chicken
episodes.overview: Bob Mortimer, Gemma Whelan, Tom Rosenthal and Lizzie Roper join Alan for amusingly aimless banter, which veers from Game of Thrones to shoplifting and mistaken identity.

episodes.name: Free Pussy
episodes.overview: Annie Siddons, Patrick Kielty, Katherine Ryan and Joe Lycett join Alan to muse on parking tickets and plane crashes.

episodes.name: Frank Bruno Was the Original Bus Driver
episodes.overview: Melanie C, Jamali Maddix, Jessica Knappett and Ardal O'Hanlon join Alan to chat about, well, whatever they fancy. The Nazis, bad funerals and the Spice Girls, for instance.

episodes.name: The Poxed Puppies of Leprous Bitches
episodes.overview: David Baddiel joins Alan to relive those glory days of Euro '96. The witty chat doesn't end there as Sindhu Vee, Elis James and Beattie Edmondson discuss celebs and B&Bs.

episodes.name: Roll Your Trousers Up and Do a Krankie
Chin Chin Bitches
episodes.overview: Swapping stories tonight are Darren Harriott, Sarah Keyworth, Angela Scanlon and Dara O Briain discussing, well, anything funny.

episodes.name: Go Ahead, Motorboat Me
episodes.overview: Helen Bauer, Rachel Fairburn, Phil Wang and Harry Hill join Alan Davies to dish the dirt on a petulant MP; a brusque burlesque dancer from Essex; a salacious encounter against the wall; and a room of rowdy revellers desperate for BEDS.

episodes.name: Full Arse in the Bin
episodes.overview: Laura Smyth, Tez Ilyas, Sara Pascoe and Adrian Edmondson join Alan to swap stories about beating Jagger, being too handsome for Jemima, snogging Joni and the lowdown Hugh Grant's exclusive parties.

episodes.name: Powerful Exposed Lips
episodes.overview: Alan Davies is joined by Catherine Bohart, Chris McCausland, Thanyia Moore and Joe Lycett. Tonight's revelations include problematic gingers, feet fetishes, and mountaineering mishaps.

episodes.name: I Scribbled on the Other Breast
episodes.overview: Alan Davies plays host to stand-up comics Babatundé Aléshé, Sara Barron, Grace Campbell and Lee Mack. The conversation ricochets between revelations about R.E.M. Darius Vassell, Transport for London and Tony Blair's New Labour.

episodes.name: My Vagina Smells of Sausages
episodes.overview: Jason Manford opens up about how he became a stand-up and the time he got a dressing down from showbiz royalty, Bruce Forsyth. Toussaint Douglass, who is currently taking the stand-up scene by storm, chats about slipping down the pecking order. While New Yorker, Desiree Burch, discusses what life is really like on the streets of the city that never sleeps; And award-winning comic Suzi Ruffell reveals how she's still reeling over the time she was left holding her neighbour's tool.

episodes.name: Very Loud and Very Rude
episodes.overview: Pulling up a chair at Alan's table this week are Joel Dommett, Rosie Jones, Sophie Duker and John Kearns who swap stories about pulling, proposals and being unapologetic, plus insider secrets about the Houses of Parliament.

episodes.name: Don't Do a Punchline When I'm Swallowing
episodes.overview: Alan invites Munya Chawawa, Nina Conti, Morgana Robinson and Bill Bailey to join him for an evening of swapping funny stories and sharing interesting anecdotes. Tonight's tales range from Panthers to plastic surgery, practical jokes and impersonations.

episodes.name: The Accuracy of a Pigeon
episodes.overview: Andy Field, Geoff Lloyd, Lou Sanders and Guz Khan keep Alan Davies and the audience entertained with revelations ranging from pill popping to party pooping, and mini mistakes with mega consequences.

episodes.name: A Hundred Quid Nothing Nothing Vibrator
episodes.overview: Richard Ayoade, Harriet Kemsley, Joanne McNally and Jonny Pelham humour us with stories about bikini beach babes, psycho-exs, getting arrested and problems at a massage parlour.

episodes.name: Magaluf And A Busy Nose
episodes.overview: Joining Alan Davies at the table are: actor, comedian, writer and presenter, Sue Perkins; award-winning hot shot comic, Lara Ricote; cutting edge stand-up, Jamali Maddix; and the Mancunian ray of sunshine that is Josh Jones. The conversation ricochets between revelations about nuns, nun chucks, Mexican soap royalty, hallucinogens, sun beds and foam parties...

episodes.name: You'll Knock The Park Out Of The Ball
episodes.overview: Jason Byrne, Fatiha El-Ghorri, Helen Bauer and Alex Jones join Alan to discuss everything from favours for Bono and Uncle David's funeral to the beastly one-armed bandit.

episodes.name: Well, Well, Well, We Seem To Have Caught Ourselves A Twat
episodes.overview: Stephen Mangan, Isy Suttie, Jordan Gray and Seann Walsh join Alan Davies to discuss everything from time keeping, bathroom habits, mistaken identity, and Jesus Christ.

episodes.name: Français Champignon
episodes.overview: Swapping stories with Alan tonight are Jessica Hynes, Emmanuel Sonubi, Amy Gledhill and Patrick Kielty. Jessica opens up about the pains of turning fifty; Amy brings tales of a trip to Reunion Island; cutting-edge stand-up Emmanuel recalls meeting his hero, Denzel Washington, and Patrick compares life in the US to the UK and what really happened to Harry Kane's shirts.

episodes.name: Groped The King
episodes.overview: With guests Al Murray, Fern Brady, London Hughes and Russell Kane.

episodes.name: "I Come From Hastings!"
episodes.overview: With guests Ola Labib, Jack Rooke, Darren Harriott and Jo Brand.

episodes.name: I Like It Dry
episodes.overview: With guests Archie Maddocks, Ed Byrne, Matt Edmondson and Steph McGovern.

episodes.name: "Your Man, Your Woman, Your Whatever...?"
episodes.overview: With guests Johnny Vegas, Rachel Parris, Ellie Taylor and Josh Pugh.

episodes.name: Unseen Clips (Season 7)
episodes.overview: Unseen footage from season 7, with guests including Rachel Parris, Jason Byrne, London Hughes, Seann Walsh, Jessica Hynes, Ola Labib and Russell Kane.

7.name: Season 7
7.overview: A seventh series was recorded at the Battersea Arts Centre. It was broadcast starting in March 2023.
